Sculptor->Save

This allows the user to save parts of the current scene to a separate
file (different from the project scene file). By default, these files
are saved in the project scene folder. This operation allows the user
to create a library of objects, or save off multiple versions, while
keeping the current scene uncluttered.
  
You can save the entire scene (objects, lights, environment, etc), or
just all the objects, or just the object selected. While using the
Potter tool (see Potter) you can also save profile/section spline
curves. You can save it in any one of the supported file formats
(Inventor Binary is the default , and also the fastest to save and
reload). You just have to type in a name (Example: dinosaur), and
Movieola will automatically add the extensions for file type and file
format (Example: dinosaur.object.iv).
